Subject to the provisions of this Act—
(a) where a contributor who ceased to pay contributions before the 1st April, 1960, dies leaving one or more beneficiaries, such beneficiary , or each of such beneficiaries, as the case may be, shall receive a pension calculated in accordance with— (i) the provisions of this Act; and (ii) the pensions tables and instructions; which were in force immediately prior to the said date;
