(2) The pensions to which subsection (1) applies are— (a) all pensions being paid under the provisions of this Act on the 31st December, 1957, the increase to take effect from the 1st January, 1958; (b) registered pensions of officers who had ceased to contribute on or before the 31st December, 1957, in so far as they relate to contributions which accrued to the Government of the former Protectorate of Northern Rhodesia; (c) those parts of the registered pensions of officers still contributing on the 1st January, 1958, purchased by contributions which fell due on or before the 31st December, 1957, in so far as they relate to contributions which have accrued to the Governments .
